content.description: Lowball DWS, really only 2-3 moves to get over the arete bulge. Start below the arete. Check your landing area for submerged rocks and logs.Problem may not always be accessible due to water level fluctuation. Accessible at 4,620 acre-feet. https://waterdata.usgs.gov/az/nwis/uv?site_no=09398300
content.location: South shore of the second meander heading towards the dam from the boat launch. (34.5573061, -111.1946017)

content.description: Ascend the slightly overhung face on positive jugs and crimps to a slopey top out. Crux at the top. Check your landing area for submerged rocks and logs.Problem may not always be accessible due to water level fluctuation. Accessible at 4,620 acre-feet.https://waterdata.usgs.gov/az/nwis/uv?site_no=09398300
content.location: West of the dam on the south shoreline. Near the other boat launch boulders. (34.5529206, -111.1857870)

content.description: Slightly overhung sandstone boulder, with a tricky topout.
content.location: Located halfway between the boat launch, and the dam, directly left of Asian Equalization.

content.description: Start as low as possible on sandstone slopers, and throw for the obvious horn.
content.location: Located halfway between the launch, and the dam, on the opposite side of the launch.

content.description: Sit start in your vessel, and pull the the middle of the heavily pocketed roof.
content.location: This route is located just before the dam on the launch side of the water.

content.description: The boat launch boulders are located between the dam, and the boat launch, and landings can change as water levels change.
